Name: Brandr Lenarrdsen (my name lmfao)

Age: 22

Weight: 197 pounds
Height: 6ft
Favorite weapon: his dual axes "Póstbitinn" (Mail biter) "Blóđbréf" (Blood letter) as well as fire flasks and bear traps

Personality traits: Witty, immature/playful, short tempered

Things he hates most: cowardice, treachery, men who are more brave in word than in action,  anything that threatens Valkenheim and her people's way of life, most knights, Wu Lin

Things he loves most: His Kin (friends and family alike). His culture and traditions, the heat of battle, Feasting and partying with his people. His raven "Hrafn", His wife Mára Ericdóttir

Siblings: 2, one died of illness the other missing

Parents: Killed in Apollyon's crusade

Wife: Mára Ericdóttir (shaman/Völva)

Children: none as of now

Close friends: Arshtock, a brute of a Raider, Arvìd, a fellow Berserker, Gúnnard, a cold and calculating Highlander, and Sir Saxon, Champion of Daubany

Clan: Ygnvi, currently under the Warborn

Potential: fearless and ambitious, very skilled combatant, Nearly untouchable in a skirmish.

Weaknesses: Doesn't quite understand what "tactical retreat means". Only speaks Icelandic and a very minimal about of Latin that Saxon taught him, making communication/treaties with other factions very difficult.

SRS - Street Racing Syndicate back when the street racing scene was the thing to do. N4S Underground and Juiced were also to other competitors to this. Of course I loved them all though N4S Underground got more popularity and Juiced getting a sequel. 
This gem was forgotten about but loved this game. Story was meh, gameplay is great! With these games my favorite thing to do was to customize my vehicles. I could spend hours making cars look good. If you got a PS2 and love to customize and have a thing for racing games. It's a must have in your collection. . .

🎮The Last of Us Part II se lanzará en dos discos porque "será enorme"🎮
—————————————————————————— The Last of Us Part II se lanza el 21 de febrero y su edición física contará con dos discos, según la descripción de Best Buy. No es el primer caso -lo mismo sucedió el año pasado con Red Dead Redemption 2-, pero sí poco habitual.

Una de las razones la comentó ayer Neil Druckmann durante la presentación de su nuevo tráiler. El codirector asegura que es el juego "más ambicioso y más largo" en los 35 años de historia del estudio. "Para contar este tipo de historia el juego necesitaba ser enorme", apunta, antes de decir que lo que hemos visto en el tráiler no es más que una "pizca de la superficie de lo que el juego guarda •••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
